						<summary>

						<p>The date may be read as the 12th also. The inscription records an endowment of 3/4 <hi rend="italic">vēli</hi> of land at Nallaraiśūr to the temple of Ūruḍaiya-Paramēśvarar by Kūttan Vīmaṉ <hi rend="italic">alias</hi> Jayaṅgoṇḍaśōḻā Mārāyaṉ a <hi rend="italic">kaikkōḷa</hi> of the <hi rend="italic">Uyyakkoṇḍāṉterinda-Tirumañjanattār-vēḷam</hi>, to provide for the feeding of pilgrims visiting the place, with the rice offered to the god during the midday service.</p>						

						</summary>
